I"O<p>The past week or so I’ve been lightly addicted to playing piano. Playing piano is for some a way to cope, for others a challenge or to express themselves. For me it is a way to relax, to distract myself and feel somehow productive.</p>

<p>As an amateur, starting a piece is almost like mixing colours on a painting palette. You only have a few basic colours. If you want to paint a specific scenery, you’ll have to keep to some basic mixes occasionally adding a random dot of colour to accentuate some elements.</p>

<p><img src="/img/palette.jpg" alt="blogfolio" /></p>

<p>The basic colours are in this case the white keys</p>

